        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/fieldset.1.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>Below the tab are the input fields. These are arranged in frames, sometimes nested some levels deep. What is inside a frame belongs together.</para>
        <para>Each frame has a label. On this label there may be a question mark signalling that information about how to input information in the fields inside the frame.</para>
        <para>On the label there may also be a button with a '+' sign. This is for repeating a frame. In the frame shown above there is only room for one name, but if a monograph has two authors, you can cause the frame to be repeated by clicking the '+' button, giving you two frames for Names and Roles and allowing you to input two authors.</para>
